a z-visa only gets you into the country for 30 days; once you are there, the employer gets you a residence permit. this is effectively a multiple-entry visa; you can leave china and return using it. some local visa offices will refuse to issue a residence permit if you entered china on a tourist (l) visa. in those cases, you have to enter on a z-visa. these are only issued outside china, so obtaining one will likely require a departure from the mainland, for example to a neighbouring country. (note that in korea, tourists not holding an alien registration card 